spans.text: Who praises , in this sauce-enamoured age ,
were it said , " GARGILIUS dined on beef , and eat brown bread
no truffles , rich ragouts — nor HULSE
her sparkling eyes to heaven , Most nunlike
More than fierce Arabs , or proud tyrants
The thrills , he swears , soft-stealing to his breast , Are lullabies , to sooth his cares to rest
, he swears , soft-stealing to his breast
! all prate , and smile , Supreme of beaux , great bulwarks of our isle
( cries the manling ) to command A conquering host , or save a sinking land , Than furl fair FLAVIA'S fan , or lead a dance , Or broach new-minted FASHIONS fresh from FRANCE
empty coxcombs more important struts , Prescribe new rules for knots , hoops
the plain For many a league , emerging flows again
( like Fortune fond to joke ) Some reigning dress
sip citron-drams , And hide their lovely locks with heads of rams

more beloved than wives , Why weeping virtue exiled , flattery thrives , Why mad for pensions , BRITONS young and old Adore base ministers , those calves of gold , Why witling templars on religion joke , Fat , rosy justices , drink , doze , and smoke , Dull critics on best bards pour
